@startuml
title REQ-013 Video Render Flow - Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "render-video.bat" as Bat
participant "render-video.mjs" as Script
participant "@remotion/bundler" as Bundler
participant "@remotion/renderer" as Renderer
participant "Root.tsx" as Root
participant "calculateMetadata" as CalcMeta
participant "Video.tsx" as Video
participant "Scene Components" as Scenes
database "output/" as Output

User -> Bat : render-video.bat game_xxx.json
Bat -> Script : node render-video.mjs game_xxx.json

== Bundle Phase ==
Script -> Script : Validate script file exists
Script -> Bundler : bundle(entryPoint, { publicDir: "output/" })
Bundler --> Script : bundleLocation (temp dir)

== Render Phase ==
Script -> Renderer : renderMedia({ composition: "MasqueradeVideo",\n  inputProps: { scriptFile }, codec: "h264", crf: 18 })

Renderer -> Root : Load composition
Root -> CalcMeta : calculateMetadata({ scriptFile })

CalcMeta -> Output : fetch scripts/game_xxx.json
Output --> CalcMeta : GameScript JSON

CalcMeta -> Output : fetch audio/{gameId}/manifest.json
Output --> CalcMeta : Audio manifest + durations

CalcMeta -> CalcMeta : buildFrameTimeline(script, audioDurations, 30)
note right: Pure function:\nCompute SceneFrameRange[]\nand totalFrames

CalcMeta --> Renderer : { durationInFrames, props }

== Frame-by-Frame Rendering ==
loop for each frame 0..totalFrames
  Renderer -> Video : render(frame)
  Video -> Video : Determine active Sequence
  Video -> Scenes : render scene component
  Scenes -> Scenes : useCurrentFrame()\nCompute visual state
  Scenes --> Video : JSX output
  Video --> Renderer : Frame pixels + audio samples
end

== Encoding ==
Renderer -> Renderer : H.264 encode\nall frames + audio mix
Renderer --> Script : Render complete

Script -> Output : Write output/videos/game_xxx.mp4
Script --> Bat : Done
Bat --> User : Video path + file size

@enduml
